abstract: Lawmakers interrogated Shou Chew over the video app’s ties to the Chinese government in a hearing that suggests the company’s problems are far from over.
snippet: Lawmakers interrogated Shou Chew over the video app’s ties to the Chinese government in a hearing that suggests the company’s problems are far from over.
lead_paragraph: The C.E.O. of TikTok was grilled for nearly five hours in Congress on Thursday about his company’s ties to China, and his testimony did little to suggest the video platform’s problems are over. The aggressive questioning of Shou Chew has only added fuel to fiery U.S.-China relations and highlighted TikTok’s awkward position as a battleground between Washington and Beijing. The Biden administration wants TikTok’s Chinese owner ByteDance to sell the company or face a ban, but hours before Mr. Chew testified, China said it opposed a sale.

main: TikTok’s C.E.O. Struggles to Make His Case in Washington

abstract: Vfl Wolfsburg casts itself as an underdog in Germany and in the Champions League. That doesn’t reflect reality.
snippet: Vfl Wolfsburg casts itself as an underdog in Germany and in the Champions League. That doesn’t reflect reality.
lead_paragraph: The grounds for VfL Wolfsburg’s inferiority complex are thin, at best. This is a club that has been crowned champion of Germany in five of the last six seasons. It has reached at least the quarterfinals of the Women’s Champions League in every year of the competition’s existence. It has made five finals, and won two of them.

main: The Superteam That May Be Selling Itself Short
print_headline: In a German Factory Town, Assembling an Unsung Power

abstract: Willem Dafoe stars as an art thief who gets trapped in a penthouse in this drama.
snippet: Willem Dafoe stars as an art thief who gets trapped in a penthouse in this drama.
lead_paragraph: The art thief (a brutish Willem Dafoe) trapped in a megamillionaire’s extravagant loft knows the value of the bronze wedge he’s damaging in a desperate attempt to pry open the door. It’s one of the few pieces he intended to steal from the smart home before its security pad failed and the exits locked shut. But Vasilis Katsoupis, the director of the stark survival thriller “Inside,” deliberately withholds that the makeshift crowbar is meant to be the Lynn Chadwick piece “Paper Hat,” last auctioned at 2.5 million pounds. Katsoupis prefers his moral challenge incalculable: Do we want the art to endure or the criminal?

main: ‘Inside’ Review: Tortured Artist, Meet Tortured Man
print_headline: Stunned Thief Meets An HGTV Nightmare

abstract: The man, Federico Carboni, overcame a series of legal and bureaucratic challenges before ending his life.
snippet: The man, Federico Carboni, overcame a series of legal and bureaucratic challenges before ending his life.
lead_paragraph: ROME — For more than a year, media reports kept Italians up to date on the travails of a 44-year-old man known only as “Mario” as he sought to end his life through physician-assisted suicide. Paralyzed 12 years ago in a traffic accident, “Mario” faced a series of legal, bureaucratic and financial hurdles in his pursuit of death.

main: Man Paralyzed 12 Years Ago Becomes Italy’s First Assisted Suicide
print_headline: A Legally Assisted Suicide  Is the First to Occur in Italy
